title: Trim Height, Rear Suspension, Adjust
htmlContent:
Trim Height, Rear Suspension, Adjust

Adjustment of the trim height is not possible. Trim height, for purposes of checking geometry and making adjustments of wheel alignment and camber, must be as follows:

Front

140 mm below front end of chassis side rail.

Rear

140 mm below rear end of chassis side rail.

These measurements approximate to a load consisting of driver, passenger and half a tank of fuel.
